1
00:00:10,167 --> 00:00:11,800
<i> What's really bothering you?</i>

2
00:00:11,933 --> 00:00:14,267
<i> There's a very big problem.</i>

3
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:15,200
<i> Thea is pregnant.</i>

4
00:00:15,333 --> 00:00:16,367
<i> Edward's going to be a dad?</i>

5
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:18,567
<i> Edward isn't the father. I am.</i>

6
00:00:18,700 --> 00:00:19,700
<i> You made a fool of yourself</i>

7
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:20,867
<i>because you couldn't control
your sex drive!</i>

8
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:23,467
<i>She's doing
all this charity work,</i>

9
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:27,000
<i>but she treats Jobert
like he isn't a good person.</i>

10
00:00:27,133 --> 00:00:31,600
<i>I just happen to be attending
a Torrecampo charity event.</i>

11
00:00:31,733 --> 00:00:32,967
<i> I'm pregnant.</i>

12
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:34,567
<i> And he's the father.</i>

13
00:00:34,733 --> 00:00:36,700
<i>That's right.
I'm going to be a dad!</i>

14
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:39,033
<i>You're going to make it look
like Edward is the father.</i>

15
00:00:39,167 --> 00:00:42,100
<i>That way, the baby will still
be a legitimate Torrecampo.</i>

16
00:00:42,233 --> 00:00:45,067
<i>He'll definitely ask you
to marry him.</i>

17
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:46,133
<i> Will you marry me?</i>

18
00:00:46,267 --> 00:00:46,933
<i> Yes.</i>

19
00:00:47,067 --> 00:00:48,900
<i> Dad, that's not fair to him.</i>

20
00:00:49,033 --> 00:00:50,300
<i> Choose.</i>

21
00:00:50,433 --> 00:00:53,767
<i>Your conscience,
or Marj and your child?</i>

22
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:55,900
<i>You will never go
near Paolo again.</i>

23
00:00:56,033 --> 00:00:59,633
<i>And the real father's identity
stays a secret. Forever.</i>

24
00:01:01,233 --> 00:01:03,467
I'll get you some water, okay?

25
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:05,233
Stay right here.

26
00:01:05,367 --> 00:01:07,067
Behave, okay, Jobert?

27
00:01:07,200 --> 00:01:10,033
- Yes, Yolly.
- I'll be right back.

28
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:15,000
Pong.

29
00:01:16,533 --> 00:01:17,400
Look...

30
00:01:17,533 --> 00:01:21,900
I have an ID now.
I look handsome.

31
00:01:22,033 --> 00:01:23,367
Testudinis.

32
00:01:24,500 --> 00:01:25,667
Kingdom Animalia.

33
00:01:27,967 --> 00:01:29,833
Pong. He's Pong.

34
00:01:29,967 --> 00:01:31,700
- A turtle.
- Testudinis.

35
00:01:31,833 --> 00:01:32,900
<i> Don't! Don't!</i>

36
00:01:33,033 --> 00:01:35,133
- Kingdom Animalia.
- Don't touch Pong!

37
00:01:35,267 --> 00:01:38,767
- You'll hurt Pong!
- Kingdom Animalia.

38
00:01:38,900 --> 00:01:41,367
- Give me Pong.
- Testudinis.

39
00:01:42,667 --> 00:01:46,067
- Kingdom Animalia.
- Give him to me! Give me Pong!

40
00:01:47,100 --> 00:01:48,667
Testudinis.

41
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:50,300
Kingdom Animalia.

42
00:01:52,200 --> 00:01:53,333
Testudinis.

43
00:01:53,467 --> 00:01:54,967
- You keep talking!
- Kingdom Animalia.

44
00:01:55,100 --> 00:01:59,200
You keep talking! So noisy!

45
00:01:59,333 --> 00:02:01,900
<i>- Jobert! Jobert!
- So noisy! You keep talking!</i>

46
00:02:02,033 --> 00:02:02,933
<i> What is going on? Jobert!</i>

47
00:02:03,067 --> 00:02:03,933
He keeps saying the same thing!

48
00:02:04,067 --> 00:02:05,833
Wait! What happened?

49
00:02:05,967 --> 00:02:07,800
What happened?

50
00:02:07,933 --> 00:02:09,400
Jobert pushed me!

51
00:02:09,533 --> 00:02:10,900
- Jobert!
- He keeps talking.

52
00:02:11,033 --> 00:02:13,200
You shouldn't have pushed him!

53
00:02:13,333 --> 00:02:14,867
<i> What happened, Yolly?</i>

54
00:02:17,267 --> 00:02:19,167
Jobert, what happened?

55
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:13,100
Did you do that on purpose?

56
00:03:14,333 --> 00:03:15,700
Why are you fighting?

57
00:03:15,833 --> 00:03:18,567
And you had to do it
during my visit?

58
00:03:18,700 --> 00:03:20,667
Are you trying to embarrass me?

59
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:27,933
They took Pong without asking!

60
00:03:28,100 --> 00:03:29,933
I don't care!

61
00:03:30,067 --> 00:03:31,400
You should not be fighting,

62
00:03:31,533 --> 00:03:34,267
as it reflects badly
on my family.

63
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:36,000
He was just worried
about his pet.

64
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:37,233
And you!

65
00:03:37,367 --> 00:03:40,367
You're supposed to be watching
him! You left him alone!

66
00:03:40,500 --> 00:03:44,000
I'm sorry.
Please don't be mad at Yolly.

67
00:03:44,133 --> 00:03:46,533
Sorry?
Sorry isn't going to fix this!

68
00:03:46,667 --> 00:03:48,200
I've already been embarrassed!

69
00:03:48,333 --> 00:03:49,700
That's enough, Ma'am.
Please stop.

70
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:51,300
Please, have some mercy.

71
00:03:51,433 --> 00:03:53,467
Take him home, Yolly.

72
00:03:54,533 --> 00:03:56,767
Before I end up
doing something.

73
00:04:06,567 --> 00:04:08,433
Don't cry, okay?

74
00:04:10,700 --> 00:04:13,400
Just say sorry
to your classmate.

75
00:04:13,533 --> 00:04:17,567
So there won't be any more
problems, okay?

76
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:19,500
Come on.

77
00:04:19,633 --> 00:04:21,467
<i> It's beautiful, isn't it?</i>

78
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:23,033
Oh my gosh.

79
00:04:23,167 --> 00:04:26,267
I can't believe I'm going
to be Mrs. Torrecampo.

80
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:30,467
The diamond is striking,
admit it.

81
00:04:30,600 --> 00:04:33,467
- It's huge, right?
- Isn't it still office hours?

82
00:04:34,933 --> 00:04:36,333
Let's get back to work.

83
00:04:50,967 --> 00:04:52,300
You're something else.

84
00:04:54,533 --> 00:04:55,833
You even managed
to fool my brother

85
00:04:55,967 --> 00:04:58,300
into proposing to you.

86
00:04:58,433 --> 00:05:00,567
Shouldn't you be happy?

87
00:05:00,700 --> 00:05:02,400
You don't have anything
to worry about anymore.

88
00:05:03,467 --> 00:05:05,267
You should've just accepted
my offer.

89
00:05:06,967 --> 00:05:07,933
I would've supported you
and the baby,

90
00:05:08,067 --> 00:05:09,333
and you could've disappeared.

91
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:14,733
Your dad made
a better counteroffer.

92
00:05:14,867 --> 00:05:17,733
And that includes marrying
Edward.

93
00:05:17,867 --> 00:05:20,567
You're really going to dump
the responsibility on him?

94
00:05:22,500 --> 00:05:26,000
What makes you think you're the
only one who has a choice here?

95
00:05:27,033 --> 00:05:29,433
Don't you feel sorry
for my brother?

96
00:05:29,567 --> 00:05:31,933
You're going to lie to him
for the rest of his life.

97
00:05:34,533 --> 00:05:36,200
Wow.

98
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:38,633
The way you talk,

99
00:05:38,767 --> 00:05:41,633
it's like
I'm the only one at fault.

100
00:05:41,767 --> 00:05:43,600
Why? I've admitted my mistake.

101
00:05:44,633 --> 00:05:45,967
I was even ready to confess
to my wife.

102
00:05:47,367 --> 00:05:49,167
But because of what you did,

103
00:05:50,533 --> 00:05:52,700
you just made our sin worse.

104
00:05:55,333 --> 00:05:56,967
Because of what I did,

105
00:05:57,100 --> 00:05:58,800
you're safe from your wife.

106
00:06:00,933 --> 00:06:03,533
I agreed to marry Edward

107
00:06:03,667 --> 00:06:07,700
because I want my child
to be a legal Torrecampo.

108
00:06:07,867 --> 00:06:10,533
Because this is what
this baby deserves.

109
00:06:12,633 --> 00:06:15,633
You should be thanking me.

110
00:06:15,767 --> 00:06:18,400
You won't be separated
from our child.

111
00:06:19,433 --> 00:06:22,533
And no one will suspect a thing.

112
00:06:30,233 --> 00:06:31,900
Excuse me, Sir.

113
00:06:32,033 --> 00:06:33,833
I'm going back to work.

114
00:06:47,433 --> 00:06:48,867
<i> Marj.</i>

115
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,467
Jobert?

116
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:53,367
Are you okay?

117
00:06:54,733 --> 00:06:56,667
Why do you look restless?

118
00:07:03,567 --> 00:07:05,367
Marj?

119
00:07:06,900 --> 00:07:12,567
I want to take care
of Baby Jasmine.

120
00:07:12,700 --> 00:07:14,600
I want to help.

121
00:07:14,767 --> 00:07:16,433
Okay, okay. Come here.

122
00:07:16,567 --> 00:07:18,300
Help me swaddle her.

123
00:07:20,167 --> 00:07:21,333
Swaddle.

124
00:07:22,367 --> 00:07:25,400
Let's put the baby
in the middle.

125
00:07:29,300 --> 00:07:31,567
Her hands go in
the center, too.

126
00:07:31,700 --> 00:07:33,467
Then this side.

127
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,400
Okay, you try, Jobert.

128
00:07:36,600 --> 00:07:38,467
First...

129
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:44,367
Here, her feet.
Don't move, Baby Jasmine.

130
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:48,600
There.

131
00:07:48,767 --> 00:07:53,333
- Very good.
- She looks like a rice cake.

132
00:07:53,467 --> 00:07:55,333
She does.

133
00:07:55,467 --> 00:07:58,433
Come here. Carry Baby Jasmine.

134
00:07:58,567 --> 00:08:00,033
Okay. Come on.

135
00:08:00,167 --> 00:08:02,000
Slowly. There.

136
00:08:03,267 --> 00:08:04,467
There.

137
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:06,233
Okay.

138
00:08:06,367 --> 00:08:10,900
- Hold.
- There. Very good.

139
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:15,200
- Lift her a little.
- She's heavy.

140
00:08:15,333 --> 00:08:16,633
<i> Heavy?</i>

141
00:08:16,767 --> 00:08:19,467
Hello, Baby Jasmine.

142
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:22,767
<i> Marj.</i>

143
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:26,267
Mom, do you need something?

144
00:08:28,067 --> 00:08:29,800
I saw you with your brother
in the nursery.

145
00:08:31,133 --> 00:08:34,767
Are you really letting Jobert
carry my granddaughter?

146
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:37,600
What if he hurts Jasmine?

147
00:08:37,733 --> 00:08:40,400
Mom, Jobert would never hurt
anyone.

148
00:08:40,533 --> 00:08:43,100
He's very gentle.

149
00:08:43,233 --> 00:08:45,100
What if he suddenly
has an epileptic attack

150
00:08:45,233 --> 00:08:47,967
and drops the baby?

151
00:08:48,100 --> 00:08:51,233
I told him he's not allowed
to carry her.

152
00:08:51,367 --> 00:08:53,200
He can only watch.

153
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:55,467
And what if he still does it?

154
00:08:55,633 --> 00:08:58,333
What if he has
one of his episodes

155
00:08:58,467 --> 00:09:00,633
and attacks my granddaughter?

156
00:09:01,733 --> 00:09:03,900
Mom, my brother
is not violent.

157
00:09:04,033 --> 00:09:06,633
He would never hurt Jasmine.

158
00:09:06,767 --> 00:09:08,167
That's what you think.

159
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:10,533
Do you know he hurt a classmate?

160
00:09:10,667 --> 00:09:12,500
I saw it
when I visited his school.

161
00:09:12,633 --> 00:09:14,967
What if he does the same
to my granddaughter?

162
00:09:15,100 --> 00:09:17,800
Mom, I know my brother.

163
00:09:17,933 --> 00:09:20,133
I raised him.

164
00:09:20,267 --> 00:09:27,200
He would never hurt anyone
unless he was hurt first.

165
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:29,400
You can't be sure of that.

166
00:09:29,567 --> 00:09:31,000
Your brother is abnormal.

167
00:09:31,133 --> 00:09:33,033
We don't know
what he's capable of.

168
00:09:33,167 --> 00:09:37,100
Excuse me. Please don't call
my brother abnormal!

169
00:09:38,133 --> 00:09:42,500
How dare you raise your voice
at me in my own house?

170
00:09:42,633 --> 00:09:45,833
You have no manners!
You don't respect me at all!

171
00:09:49,367 --> 00:09:50,333
You know what?

172
00:09:50,467 --> 00:09:53,100
I was right about you all along.

173
00:09:53,233 --> 00:09:56,867
I regret ever agreeing
to let you marry my son.

174
00:10:07,133 --> 00:10:09,533
How dare your wife yell at me

175
00:10:09,667 --> 00:10:13,467
when all I've ever been
to her is kind?

176
00:10:14,767 --> 00:10:17,200
Are you sure
she actually yelled at you?

177
00:10:17,333 --> 00:10:19,833
Maybe she just raised her voice?

178
00:10:19,967 --> 00:10:21,667
And what do you call
raising her voice?

179
00:10:23,167 --> 00:10:25,667
So are you saying I'm lying?

180
00:10:26,567 --> 00:10:28,500
That's not what I mean, Mom.

181
00:10:28,633 --> 00:10:32,200
I'm just concerned
about my granddaughter

182
00:10:32,333 --> 00:10:34,367
getting hurt because of Jobert.

183
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:36,100
I have every reason
to be concerned.

184
00:10:36,267 --> 00:10:38,300
He has a history
of hurting people.

185
00:10:38,433 --> 00:10:39,333
And then all of a sudden,

186
00:10:39,467 --> 00:10:41,700
your wife starts shouting
and getting angry.

187
00:10:43,067 --> 00:10:44,833
I understand your concern.

188
00:10:46,600 --> 00:10:48,100
I'll clarify everything
with Marj.

189
00:10:48,233 --> 00:10:52,267
You have a perfectly
valid reason to worry.

190
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:55,033
What I just don't understand

191
00:10:55,167 --> 00:10:58,300
is why Marj would suddenly
get mad like that.

192
00:10:58,433 --> 00:11:00,633
Maybe your wife is crazy?

193
00:11:01,633 --> 00:11:05,300
When she's in front of you,
she acts all sweet.

194
00:11:05,433 --> 00:11:09,433
But when you're not looking,
she changes. Oh, please.

195
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:12,933
Maybe you said something bad
about her?

196
00:11:13,067 --> 00:11:15,367
Marj wouldn't react like
that for no reason.

197
00:11:15,867 --> 00:11:17,700
So now it's my fault?

198
00:11:17,833 --> 00:11:20,400
Paolo, I'm the victim here.

199
00:11:20,533 --> 00:11:23,733
The victim
of your ill-mannered wife.

200
00:11:26,767 --> 00:11:28,567
Okay. I'll talk to her.

201
00:11:33,100 --> 00:11:38,233
Love, it's not right for your
mom to call my brother abnormal.

202
00:11:38,367 --> 00:11:43,400
She insulted Jobert.
How could I not get mad?

203
00:11:43,567 --> 00:11:45,900
I knew it. Oh, my mom.

204
00:11:46,167 --> 00:11:47,800
But let's face it.

205
00:11:47,933 --> 00:11:50,267
She's right to be concerned

206
00:11:50,567 --> 00:11:52,533
about Jobert being left alone
with Jasmine.

207
00:11:54,033 --> 00:11:57,867
I know Jobert
doesn't hurt anyone

208
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,400
unless he feels threatened.

209
00:11:59,533 --> 00:12:01,700
But it's still not safe.

210
00:12:01,833 --> 00:12:05,400
What if he suddenly drops
Baby Jasmine

211
00:12:05,533 --> 00:12:06,867
during an epileptic attack?

212
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:10,633
Jobert knows he's not allowed
to carry Jasmine.

213
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:14,000
That's not even the point, Love.

214
00:12:15,833 --> 00:12:18,667
Have you talked to Jobert
about what happened earlier?

215
00:12:18,800 --> 00:12:22,900
I'm about to.
But please trust me.

216
00:12:23,033 --> 00:12:25,233
Jobert would never do anything
to hurt Jasmine.

217
00:12:25,367 --> 00:12:27,867
He loves our daughter so much.

218
00:12:28,000 --> 00:12:31,100
Exactly. He's very fond of her.

219
00:12:31,233 --> 00:12:33,100
What if he can't control himself

220
00:12:33,233 --> 00:12:36,700
and suddenly picks her up
and hugs her too tightly?

221
00:12:40,933 --> 00:12:42,600
Love,

222
00:12:42,733 --> 00:12:46,133
there's nothing wrong
with being extra careful.

223
00:12:46,267 --> 00:12:48,000
What do you want me to do?

224
00:12:49,067 --> 00:12:51,433
Hide Jasmine from Jobert?

225
00:12:51,567 --> 00:12:53,967
- Keep him away?
- No.

226
00:12:54,100 --> 00:12:55,767
Okay? Just as much as possible,

227
00:12:55,900 --> 00:12:59,733
maybe don't leave Jobert alone
with Baby Jasmine.

228
00:13:01,500 --> 00:13:03,100
Please.

229
00:13:03,233 --> 00:13:04,833
Fine.

230
00:13:04,967 --> 00:13:09,300
But what your mom said
about Jobert was still wrong.

231
00:13:09,433 --> 00:13:12,900
I know. I'll talk to her.

232
00:13:13,033 --> 00:13:15,633
Let's just try
to keep the peace.

233
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,333
Jobert?

234
00:13:42,300 --> 00:13:45,000
Jobert, are you still not okay?

235
00:13:49,867 --> 00:13:51,267
Jobert.

236
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:53,500
I'm bad.

237
00:13:53,800 --> 00:13:56,900
I'm bad for Baby Jasmine.

238
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:03,133
Hey, don't say that.
You're not bad.

239
00:14:03,267 --> 00:14:06,933
You were just defending
yourself, right?

240
00:14:07,067 --> 00:14:09,300
You even apologized
to your classmate.

241
00:14:12,067 --> 00:14:13,433
Jobert.

242
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:16,400
Jobert.

243
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:25,433
They said I'm bad.

244
00:14:25,567 --> 00:14:28,767
Paolo's mom said so.

245
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:33,467
She said I'm not normal.

246
00:14:34,633 --> 00:14:38,600
She said I'm bad
for Baby Jasmine.

247
00:14:40,500 --> 00:14:44,500
That's not true. Don't say that.

248
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:46,967
- I'm bad.
- You're not bad. No.

249
00:14:48,033 --> 00:14:51,833
Son, you're very kind.

250
00:14:51,967 --> 00:14:53,767
You're hardworking.

251
00:14:53,900 --> 00:14:55,700
You love everyone.

252
00:14:57,033 --> 00:15:00,133
Jasmine is so lucky
to have you as her uncle.

253
00:15:00,267 --> 00:15:02,367
Okay?

254
00:15:05,033 --> 00:15:07,300
You're different, yes.

255
00:15:07,433 --> 00:15:10,633
But remember this, okay?

256
00:15:10,767 --> 00:15:12,567
You are normal.

257
00:15:13,900 --> 00:15:16,200
You're special.

258
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:19,500
Even more special
than a lot of people out there.

259
00:15:24,533 --> 00:15:27,833
Jobert, listen to me.

260
00:15:27,967 --> 00:15:29,300
Repeat what I say.

261
00:15:29,433 --> 00:15:31,133
I am not bad.

262
00:15:31,267 --> 00:15:32,633
Come on, say it.

263
00:15:32,767 --> 00:15:34,200
Dear, say it. Come on.

264
00:15:34,333 --> 00:15:35,533
I am not bad.

265
00:15:37,133 --> 00:15:40,133
- I am not bad.
- That's right.

266
00:15:40,267 --> 00:15:42,300
I am special.

267
00:15:42,433 --> 00:15:44,567
I am special.

268
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:46,433
I am a good uncle.

269
00:15:47,467 --> 00:15:48,700
I am a good uncle.

270
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:53,100
You're a good uncle.

271
00:15:53,233 --> 00:15:55,067
You're a good boy.

272
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:56,600
You're not bad.

273
00:16:19,467 --> 00:16:22,033
Jobert, I'm just going
downstairs, okay?

274
00:16:22,167 --> 00:16:25,667
I'm going to sterilize
Jasmine's bottles.

275
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:27,467
I'll be right back.

276
00:16:27,600 --> 00:16:29,333
Yes, Marj.

277
00:16:49,933 --> 00:16:51,233
Baby?

278
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:00,633
Baby Jasmine,
why are you crying?

279
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:03,867
Baby?

280
00:17:05,367 --> 00:17:07,067
Marj!

281
00:17:07,200 --> 00:17:10,933
Weng, after that,
can you vacuum our room again?

282
00:17:11,067 --> 00:17:12,733
There's still some dust.

283
00:17:12,867 --> 00:17:14,667
Yes, Ma'am.
I'll take care of it.

284
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,533
- Thank you.
- Okay, Ma'am.

285
00:17:18,167 --> 00:17:19,867
Marj...

286
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,233
where's Jasmine?

287
00:17:22,367 --> 00:17:24,167
She's in the room, Mom.
Sleeping.

288
00:17:24,300 --> 00:17:26,500
Who's with her?

289
00:17:26,633 --> 00:17:31,100
Baby Jasmine,
why are you crying?

290
00:17:46,067 --> 00:17:48,833
Baby Jasmine, look.

291
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:51,200
Cute bear.

292
00:17:52,667 --> 00:17:54,167
I'm coming back.

293
00:17:54,300 --> 00:17:56,100
My brother's with her.

294
00:17:56,233 --> 00:17:58,667
Marj, why would you leave her
with Jobert?

295
00:17:58,800 --> 00:18:00,800
Didn't I tell you
not to do that?

296
00:18:00,933 --> 00:18:03,667
And Paolo already told you, too!
Come on!

297
00:18:14,067 --> 00:18:16,767
I did a good job.

298
00:18:16,900 --> 00:18:19,800
I helped Baby Jasmine.

299
00:18:19,933 --> 00:18:22,433
She's not crying anymore.

300
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:25,533
I'll put it here.

301
00:18:25,667 --> 00:18:28,933
So you won't cry anymore.

302
00:18:29,067 --> 00:18:32,267
So Baby Jasmine can be happy.

303
00:18:44,500 --> 00:18:45,900
Jasmine!

304
00:18:46,033 --> 00:18:48,100
My granddaughter!

305
00:18:48,233 --> 00:18:49,200
What were you thinking?

306
00:18:49,333 --> 00:18:52,067
Why would you leave her here
with your brother?

307
00:18:52,200 --> 00:18:53,567
Baby!

308
00:18:54,967 --> 00:18:55,733
What?

309
00:18:55,867 --> 00:18:58,067
Mom, I was only gone
for a second.

310
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:01,900
- Cry...
- You!

311
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:05,233
What did you do
to my granddaughter?

312
00:19:05,600 --> 00:19:08,100
She almost suffocated!

313
00:19:08,233 --> 00:19:11,433
Mom, please,
my brother didn't mean it.

314
00:19:11,567 --> 00:19:14,733
- He didn't do it on purpose.
- What if Jasmine got hurt?

315
00:19:15,600 --> 00:19:18,567
I'm not bad. No.

316
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:20,567
I'm not bad.

317
00:19:20,700 --> 00:19:22,400
He didn't mean it!

318
00:19:22,533 --> 00:19:23,767
But what if she did get hurt?

319
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:27,100
Throw your brother out!

320
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:30,233
Kick him out!

321
00:19:33,033 --> 00:19:35,167
Give me Jasmine! Bring her here!

322
00:19:35,300 --> 00:19:36,267
Yolly!

323
00:19:38,600 --> 00:19:42,233
Sorry. Sorry, Marj.
I didn't mean it.

324
00:19:42,367 --> 00:19:43,867
It's okay, it's okay.

325
00:19:45,900 --> 00:19:48,300
I know you didn't mean it.

326
00:19:48,433 --> 00:19:50,900
It's okay. Calm down.

327
00:19:57,333 --> 00:20:00,000
Jobert didn't do anything wrong,
Mom.

328
00:20:00,133 --> 00:20:02,700
He just didn't understand
what he was doing.

329
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:04,967
You know what? You're right.

330
00:20:05,100 --> 00:20:06,967
It's your fault.

331
00:20:07,100 --> 00:20:10,967
Enough. You didn't do anything
wrong. It's not your fault.

332
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:12,833
Stop crying.

333
00:20:12,967 --> 00:20:14,267
Okay?

334
00:20:14,400 --> 00:20:17,400
Bad. I'm a bad uncle.

335
00:20:17,533 --> 00:20:21,067
I didn't know.

336
00:20:21,200 --> 00:20:22,767
Baby Jasmine.

337
00:20:22,900 --> 00:20:25,300
No. That's not true. No.

338
00:20:25,433 --> 00:20:28,800
- Bad!
- No. You're not bad.

339
00:20:28,933 --> 00:20:31,133
- Stop. Jobert is a good boy.
- I'm a bad uncle!

340
00:20:31,267 --> 00:20:35,233
- No.
- I almost killed Baby Jasmine!

341
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:37,033
Bad!

342
00:20:37,167 --> 00:20:39,500
- Jobert is a good boy.
- It's not your fault.

343
00:20:39,633 --> 00:20:41,200
- It's not your fault. Enough!
- Bad uncle!

344
00:20:41,333 --> 00:20:44,767
- That's enough! That's enough!
- Bad uncle!

345
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:47,767
That's enough, okay? Stop!

346
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:49,000
I told you before

347
00:20:49,133 --> 00:20:50,433
to keep Jobert away
from my granddaughter.

348
00:20:50,567 --> 00:20:52,267
Did you listen? No, right?

349
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,500
You even acted proud about it.

350
00:20:53,633 --> 00:20:57,767
Then you made me look like
the villain in front of my son.

351
00:20:57,900 --> 00:21:00,133
Mom, I only told Paolo
the truth.

352
00:21:00,267 --> 00:21:01,133
And what did he say to you?

353
00:21:01,267 --> 00:21:02,333
Didn't he tell you to follow
what I said?

354
00:21:02,467 --> 00:21:03,867
You said you would.
But did you? No.

355
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:05,233
You still disobeyed him.

356
00:21:05,367 --> 00:21:06,933
If you had just listened to me,
Marj,

357
00:21:07,067 --> 00:21:09,333
this wouldn't have happened.

358
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:11,800
You just wanted to help.
It's not your fault.

359
00:21:11,933 --> 00:21:13,733
- You didn't mean it.
- Bad!

360
00:21:13,867 --> 00:21:15,600
- Bad!
- Stop it!

361
00:21:15,733 --> 00:21:17,933
- Bad!
- Enough, enough.

362
00:21:18,067 --> 00:21:18,933
Stop crying. Calm down.

363
00:21:19,067 --> 00:21:20,533
- Jobert, stop.
- Calm down.

364
00:21:20,667 --> 00:21:23,233
- That's enough!
- Enough!

365
00:21:23,367 --> 00:21:27,167
- Stop!
- That's enough!

366
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:33,167
Good boy. Jobert is a good boy.

367
00:21:33,300 --> 00:21:34,867
Yes, Mom, I'll take the blame
for everything,

368
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:37,167
but please don't drag my brother
into this.

369
00:21:37,300 --> 00:21:40,100
He would never want Jasmine
to get hurt.

370
00:21:40,233 --> 00:21:42,900
Nobody wants anyone to get hurt.

371
00:21:47,867 --> 00:21:48,767
Mom.

372
00:21:48,900 --> 00:21:50,600
What's going on?
Why are you fighting?

373
00:21:50,733 --> 00:21:52,167
Your wife disobeyed you.

374
00:21:52,300 --> 00:21:54,067
That's why Jasmine
was put in danger.

375
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:56,400
What?

376
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:07,400
It's just upsetting.

377
00:22:07,533 --> 00:22:08,500
We already agreed

378
00:22:08,633 --> 00:22:11,267
you wouldn't leave Baby Jasmine
alone with Jobert.

379
00:22:11,400 --> 00:22:12,700
But you still did.

380
00:22:13,167 --> 00:22:15,533
Love, I admit it's my fault.

381
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:19,000
I just got overwhelmed.

382
00:22:20,067 --> 00:22:21,233
I feel like
I'm walking on eggshells

383
00:22:21,367 --> 00:22:23,000
whenever your mom is around.

384
00:22:23,300 --> 00:22:25,500
There's so much to think about,
so much to do.

385
00:22:25,833 --> 00:22:27,733
I get rattled.

386
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:32,300
I know.

387
00:22:32,667 --> 00:22:34,233
I know, okay?

388
00:22:34,533 --> 00:22:36,800
And I'm sorry.

389
00:22:36,933 --> 00:22:37,867
I'm sorry I'm not there

390
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:41,467
when I promised
I wouldn't leave you alone.

391
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:46,000
I know it's your responsibility
to provide for the family.

392
00:22:46,133 --> 00:22:47,967
I understand that.

393
00:22:49,100 --> 00:22:50,367
Okay.

394
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:52,533
Tell me.

395
00:22:52,667 --> 00:22:54,167
Tell me how I can help you.

396
00:22:56,300 --> 00:23:00,533
Paolo, you know Jobert.
He would never hurt Jasmine.

397
00:23:02,567 --> 00:23:04,333
I know.

398
00:23:04,467 --> 00:23:07,467
But, Love,
you also need to accept...

399
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:09,300
that you were wrong
about Jobert.

400
00:23:10,367 --> 00:23:12,167
Yes, he didn't mean it.

401
00:23:13,300 --> 00:23:16,333
But that doesn't mean
he can't accidentally hurt her.

402
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:20,500
I think...

403
00:23:20,633 --> 00:23:24,133
it's time we make sure
this never happens again.

404
00:23:26,233 --> 00:23:27,967
What are you saying?

405
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:32,033
I'm saying maybe...

406
00:23:32,933 --> 00:23:34,933
Jobert should stay with your mom
for now.

407
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:38,900
Don't do that to me.

408
00:23:39,033 --> 00:23:42,000
You can't separate me
from my brother.

409
00:23:42,133 --> 00:23:43,367
Love, just until Baby Jasmine
gets stronger

410
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:44,733
and a little older.

411
00:23:44,867 --> 00:23:46,867
No. No, Paolo!

412
00:23:48,333 --> 00:23:50,600
This is for the best.

413
00:23:50,733 --> 00:23:53,100
For Baby Jasmine.

414
00:23:53,233 --> 00:23:55,267
He can't stay with my dad.

415
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:59,033
You know he'll just hurt him
there. You know that.

416
00:24:00,633 --> 00:24:03,600
Jobert's older now.
He can defend himself.

417
00:24:03,733 --> 00:24:08,133
Unlike Baby Jasmine.
She's still so fragile.

418
00:24:09,467 --> 00:24:11,600
Love, I know.

419
00:24:11,733 --> 00:24:16,033
I know it hurts you to be
separated from your brother.

420
00:24:16,167 --> 00:24:20,033
And it hurts me, too,
because I care about Jobert.

421
00:24:20,167 --> 00:24:23,200
But we have to make sacrifices.

422
00:24:23,333 --> 00:24:27,400
To make sure Baby Jasmine
is safe.

423
00:24:35,233 --> 00:24:38,333
Please.
Just give me some time to think.

424
00:24:52,200 --> 00:24:54,233
<i>I don't know what to do anymore,
Mom.</i>

425
00:24:55,267 --> 00:24:56,667
I feel trapped.

426
00:24:56,800 --> 00:24:59,267
I don't want
Jobert away from me.

427
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:02,300
He's been with me my whole life.

428
00:25:02,467 --> 00:25:04,767
If this happens,

429
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:06,400
it'll be the first time
we've ever been apart.

430
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:10,567
I know, Marj.

431
00:25:10,700 --> 00:25:15,033
You're feeling pressured by
Paolo and his mom, aren't you?

432
00:25:18,000 --> 00:25:20,567
I want to protect Jasmine, too,
Mom.

433
00:25:22,733 --> 00:25:25,300
What if, Marj, for example...

434
00:25:27,133 --> 00:25:30,400
What if maybe you just agree
to what they want?

435
00:25:30,533 --> 00:25:32,533
What if...

436
00:25:32,667 --> 00:25:35,467
you just don't let Jobert
get close to Jasmine?

437
00:25:36,667 --> 00:25:39,600
He can still live with you.

438
00:25:39,733 --> 00:25:41,800
He just won't be allowed

439
00:25:41,933 --> 00:25:45,733
to take care of the baby
or play with her.

440
00:25:47,967 --> 00:25:50,733
That way he's still here, but...

441
00:25:52,067 --> 00:25:53,633
there won't be any more trouble.
Right, Marj?

442
00:25:54,667 --> 00:25:56,467
Right?

443
00:25:57,500 --> 00:25:59,567
I hope they'll agree to that.

444
00:25:59,700 --> 00:26:03,233
Marj, I'm sorry
I can't help you, dear.

445
00:26:03,367 --> 00:26:07,433
You know the history between
your dad and Jobert.

446
00:26:09,267 --> 00:26:13,567
Mom, I will never let Jobert
go back there.

447
00:26:13,700 --> 00:26:16,333
I'll find another way.

448
00:26:28,300 --> 00:26:32,000
Does Paolo
not love me anymore?

449
00:26:32,133 --> 00:26:33,133
It's not like that.

450
00:26:33,267 --> 00:26:36,400
I just want to protect
Baby Jasmine.

451
00:26:36,533 --> 00:26:39,367
To keep her safe always.

452
00:26:39,500 --> 00:26:44,433
Then you'll do everything
for Baby Jasmine, right?

453
00:26:44,600 --> 00:26:46,300
I'm so sorry about this, Marj.

454
00:26:46,433 --> 00:26:49,533
I know I promised
that when you got married,

455
00:26:49,667 --> 00:26:52,133
you and Jobert
were a package deal.

456
00:26:52,267 --> 00:26:53,967
But I have no choice.

457
00:26:54,100 --> 00:26:55,400
Jobert needs to go.

458
00:26:55,900 --> 00:26:58,167
The doctor said
our baby is healthy.

459
00:26:58,567 --> 00:26:59,600
Don't worry.

460
00:26:59,833 --> 00:27:02,567
I just want everything to be
perfect when the baby's born.

461
00:27:02,700 --> 00:27:04,467
I have very big dreams for her.

462
00:27:04,767 --> 00:27:08,033
I just wanted to share
the first picture of your baby.

463
00:27:08,167 --> 00:27:10,000
I'm sure she'll look like you
when she comes out.

464
00:27:11,400 --> 00:27:12,267
Love...

465
00:27:13,133 --> 00:27:15,033
who's texting you?
